ce:section.ce:para:
The nonaromatic macromolecular AEEgens, i.e., M1 and M2, were synthesized by surfactant free facile polymerization of hydrophobic monomers, i.e., prop-2-enamide (PE) + butyl-2-propenoate (BP) and PE + ethylene glycol methacrylate (EGM), by in situ anchored third acrylamido-ester monomers, i.e., butyl 3-acrylamidopropanoate, BAP and ethylene glycol 3-acrylamido-2-methylpropanoate, EGAMP, using N,N′-methylenebisacrylamide (NNBIS), potassium persulfate (PP) and sodium bisulfite (SB) as crosslinker, initiator and coinitiator, respectively. In a glass reactor, 30 mL Y1
                         mol BP/ EGM, 8 mL Y2
                         mol PE, and 7 mL Y3
                         mmol NNBIS were mixed in water at 350 rpm (Scheme 1). The solution was homogenized in presence of inert N2 for 10 h (Table 1
                        ). The reaction was initiated by the gradual addition of 10 mL aqueous PP (Y4
                        ) + SB (Y5
                        ) (Table 1). The as-prepared M1 and M2 (Scheme 1) were swelled in 3:1 (v/v) water/methanol solution to remove undesired components. Finally, M1 and M2 were dried under vacuum. The crosslink densities (ρc
                        ) of M1 and M2 were calculated using a previously reported method [50].
